===Etymology===
Old English [[scyrte]], from Germanic ''*skurtijon''.  Cognate with Dutch [[schort]], German [[Schürze]] ‘apron’.  [[skirt|Skirt]] is a parallel formation from Old Norse; compare also [[short]], from the same ultimate source.

